&lt;h2&gt;Stack&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://reactjs.org/&quot;&gt;React&lt;/a&gt; was used to build the views and display blockchain data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://redux.js.org/&quot;&gt;Redux&lt;/a&gt; was used as the state container along with &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/trufflesuite/drizzle&quot;&gt;Drizzle&lt;/a&gt; to sync with the state of the deployed smart contract. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://solidity.readthedocs.io/&quot;&gt;Solidity&lt;/a&gt; was used to develop the smart contract containing the business logic.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://truffleframework.com/&quot;&gt;Truffle&lt;/a&gt; was used to deploy SmartCert on the Ropsten test net.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h1&gt;Contribute&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I’m open to any and all contribution! Find the repo &lt;a href=&quot;https://gitlab.com/sliptype/smartcert&quot;&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</content:encoded></item><item><title><![CDATA[Tacky]]></title><description><![CDATA[Tacky  is a scenario discovery and management tool. It allows you to create a hierarchical description of user interactions with a system…]]></description><link>https://sliptype.github.io//tacky/</link><guid isPermaLink="false">https://sliptype.github.io//tacky/</guid><pubDate>Wed, 20 Sep 2017 22:40:32 GMT</pubDate><content:encoded>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.the-tacky.com/&quot;&gt;Tacky&lt;/a&gt; is a scenario discovery and management tool. It allows you to create a hierarchical description of user interactions with a system and transform it into a list of discrete test cases.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Motivation&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The linear way of writing test scenarios leaves a lot to be desired. Representing the state of a system without abstracting away the steps to get there becomes tedious and error-prone. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;Usage&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In Tacky, you create rows (known as layers) that contain steps (known as cases). A layer can have multiple cases. For example, a todo app could look like this:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-cc1f4.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
  
  &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
    style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
      style=&quot;padding-bottom: 56.14754098360656%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        style=&quot;width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;&quot;
        alt=&quot;Tacky&quot;
        title=&quot;&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-fb8a0.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-1a291.png 148w,
/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-2bc4a.png 295w,
/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-fb8a0.png 590w,
/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-526de.png 885w,
/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-fa2eb.png 1180w,
/static/tacky-35bb635df941324433d0963c71b23ea1-cc1f4.png 1464w&quot;
        sizes=&quot;(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px&quot;
      /&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt;
  
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regarding the above as a tree, the paths that need to be followed to exhaustively test the system are those from root to leaf. A tester can mark the branches as they are completed and know at a glance which paths still need testing. Tacky can also display the branches as a list of discrete test cases:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;
  &lt;a
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-link&quot;
    href=&quot;/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-f6e09.png&quot;
    style=&quot;display: block&quot;
    target=&quot;_blank&quot;
    rel=&quot;noopener&quot;
  &gt;
  
  &lt;span
    class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-wrapper&quot;
    style=&quot;position: relative; display: block; ; max-width: 590px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;&quot;
  &gt;
    &lt;span
      class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-background-image&quot;
      style=&quot;padding-bottom: 108.75656742556919%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url(&apos;data:image/png;base64,&apos;); background-size: cover; display: block;&quot;
    &gt;
      &lt;img
        class=&quot;gatsby-resp-image-image&quot;
        style=&quot;width: 100%; height: 100%; margin: 0; vertical-align: middle; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; box-shadow: inset 0px 0px 0px 400px white;&quot;
        alt=&quot;Tacky&quot;
        title=&quot;&quot;
        src=&quot;/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-fb8a0.png&quot;
        srcset=&quot;/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-1a291.png 148w,
/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-2bc4a.png 295w,
/static/tacky2-b8d866335b76f3dabecccb99b5b6fafe-fb8a0.png 590w,
